WEBVTT

00:07.140 --> 00:17.584
JUDY WOODRUFF: A weekend of
work for world powers and Iran.
Disputes over arms embargoes

00:17.584 --> 00:21.588
and economic sanctions relief
prolong nuclear negotiations.

00:21.588 --> 00:25.392
Good evening. I'm
Judy Woodruff.

00:25.392 --> 00:29.730
Also ahead: It's Friday. David
Brooks and E.J. Dionne are here
to analyze the week's

00:29.730 --> 00:31.932
news.

00:31.932 --> 00:37.304
Plus, Serena Williams enters the
Wimbledon finals on the verge of
making history,one

00:37.304 --> 00:42.009
match away from her
second Grand Slam.

00:42.009 --> 00:52.920
And a harrowing look at the rise
and fall of British soul singer
Amy Winehouse. A

00:52.920 --> 00:56.623
documentary sheds light on the
star's talent, fame and the
addiction that cut her life
short.

01:02.162 --> 01:05.732
you how brilliant she was, and
for you to kind of fall in love
her. When you fall

01:05.732 --> 01:10.837
in love with her, then you feel
very different when you see the
archive footage of the paparazzi

01:10.837 --> 01:13.240
and her being hounded.

01:13.240 --> 01:15.175
JUDY WOODRUFF: Those are some
of the stories we're covering on
tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

01:17.611 --> 01:21.248
JUDY WOODRUFF: The head of the
federal government's personnel
office resigned today in the
wake

01:21.248 --> 01:25.552
of a massive data
breach at the agency.

01:25.552 --> 01:30.290
Katherine Archuleta stepped down
after disclosures more than 21
million current, former and
prospective

01:30.290 --> 01:34.261
federal employees were affected.

01:34.261 --> 01:38.098
White House spokesman Josh
Earnest said today the president
believes new leadership is badly

01:38.098 --> 01:40.133
need.

01:40.133 --> 01:43.804
JOSH EARNEST, White House Press
Secretary: Director Archuleta
did offer her resignation

01:43.804 --> 01:49.609
today. She did so of her own
volition. She recognizes, as
the White House does, that

01:49.609 --> 01:53.513
the urgent challenges currently
facing the Office of Personnel
Management require a manager

01:53.513 --> 01:57.217
with a specialized set of
skills and experiences.

01:57.217 --> 02:00.854
JUDY WOODRUFF: In her statement
today, Archuleta said she wants
to let the personnel office

02:00.854 --> 02:05.292
-- quote -- "move beyond
the current challenges."

02:05.292 --> 02:10.263
Federal Reserve Chair Janet
Yellen signaled today the U.S.
Central Bank is ready to raise

02:10.263 --> 02:14.835
interest rates this year. But
in a speech, she also said that
could change because the

02:14.835 --> 02:18.305
economic outlook is -- quote
-- "highly uncertain."

02:18.305 --> 02:23.877
Meanwhile, hopes for a Greek
bailout deal buoyed Wall Street.
The Dow Jones industrial

02:23.877 --> 02:31.685
average gained more than 210
points to close at 17760. The
Nasdaq rose 75 points and

02:31.685 --> 02:36.957
the S&P added 25. For the week,
the Dow gained a fraction of 1
percent. The Nasdaq

02:36.957 --> 02:40.727
and the S&P fell a fraction.

02:40.727 --> 02:45.999
It turns out that the suspect in
the church shootings in
Charleston, South Carolina,
should

02:45.999 --> 02:53.040
have been legally barred from
buying his .45-caliber handgun.
The FBI said today that a
background

02:53.040 --> 02:59.813
check failed to spot Dylann
Roof's arrest for drug
possession weeks earlier. FBI
Director

02:59.813 --> 03:05.952
James Comey said he blames
incomplete and inaccurate
paperwork.

03:05.952 --> 03:11.391
The Charleston shootings led
directly to removing the
Confederate Battle Flag from
South Carolina's

03:11.391 --> 03:18.398
state capitol grounds today. An
estimated 10,000 people cheered
and chanted as an honor

03:18.398 --> 03:21.535
guard of state troopers lowered
the banner. Longtime civil
rights activists were jubilant.

03:26.473 --> 03:31.411
for the first time in my life,
the state has said that we're
all one and all lives matter

03:31.411 --> 03:36.516
and, if it offends us, we will
take it down. And for all these
years, the state wouldn't

03:36.516 --> 03:40.253
do it. But it was done
today. It's an awesome day.

03:40.253 --> 03:44.157
JUDY WOODRUFF: The Confederate
banner had been on the state
capitol grounds for more

03:44.157 --> 03:49.429
than 50 years. After being
taken down today, it was moved
to a nearby museum.

03:49.429 --> 03:55.769
The U.S. Food and Drug
Administration is upping the
warnings on some popular
anti-inflammatory

03:55.769 --> 04:01.708
drugs. The agency says the
change affects non-aspirin
painkillers like ibuprofen and

04:01.708 --> 04:07.047
naproxen sold over the counter
and by prescription. New labels
will add to existing warnings

04:07.047 --> 04:12.052
about increased risk of
heart attack and stroke.

04:12.052 --> 04:18.592
The U.S. House of
Representatives voted
overwhelmingly today to speed
new treatments to market. The

04:18.592 --> 04:23.763
bill is meant to expedite
approval of drugs and medical
devices by the Food and Drug
Administration.

04:23.763 --> 04:30.871
It also boosts funding for
biomedical research by nearly $9
billion. Consumer groups warned

04:30.871 --> 04:34.808
that the bill will weaken
safeguards against potentially
dangerous products. The Senate

04:34.808 --> 04:38.778
has yet to take up the issue.

04:38.778 --> 04:45.785
In Yemen, fighting raged on,
even as a U.N.-brokered
humanitarian truce was supposed
to take effect.

04:45.785 --> 04:51.024
Saudi-led airstrikes blasted
Shiite rebel targets in Sanaa,
the Yemeni capital city.

04:51.024 --> 04:54.294
The rebels, in turn,
shelled the city of Aden.

04:54.294 --> 04:58.765
A U.N. spokesman said both sides
had agreed to stop fighting.

04:58.765 --> 05:03.570
AHMAD FAWZI, United Nations
Spokesman: If this humanitarian
pause is respected, during

05:03.570 --> 05:09.643
any humanitarian pause, the
humanitarian agencies and their
partners aim to reach people in

05:09.643 --> 05:12.045
need with essential supplies,
and that includes everything,
medicine, vaccination, food,
water,

05:12.045 --> 05:13.780
fuel.

05:13.780 --> 05:18.185
JUDY WOODRUFF: The truce is
supposed to last for a week, and
aims to get aid to some

05:18.185 --> 05:21.388
21 million people.

05:21.388 --> 05:26.860
The U.N. Refugee Agency sounded
the alarm today over a flood of
refugees into Greece,

05:26.860 --> 05:32.866
even as that country faces
bankruptcy. More than 77,000
migrants have landed on Greek

05:32.866 --> 05:38.538
islands this year, an average of
1,000 per day. The U.N.
appealed to the European Union

05:38.538 --> 05:41.741
to step in before the
situation gets worse.

05:41.741 --> 05:44.945
WILLIAM SPINDLER, International
Organization for Migration: We
have seen huge expressions

05:44.945 --> 05:54.354
of solidarity from the Greek
people, the Greek public,
organizing distributions of
food,

05:54.354 --> 06:01.094
water, milk for the babies and
so on, which is particularly
moving, given the economic

06:01.094 --> 06:04.731
situation in Greece. But Greece
urgently needs help, and we
expect Europe to step forward.

